üìò Security Concepts ‚Äì PG-DITISS (Aug 2025)
Session 14: Virus vs Worm, Types of Viruses, AV Evasion & Detection
üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. A computer virus differs from a worm because a virus:
A. Spreads automatically
B. Requires user action to spread
C. Is network-based only
D. Does not modify files

2. A worm primarily spreads through:
A. Email attachments only
B. User execution
C. Network vulnerabilities
D. USB devices

3. Which malware can replicate without a host file?
A. Virus
B. Trojan
C. Worm
D. Spyware

4. File infector viruses mainly target:
A. Boot sector
B. Application files
C. Network traffic
D. Hardware

5. Boot sector viruses infect:
A. Executable files
B. Master Boot Record
C. Memory only
D. Network packets

6. Macro viruses are commonly associated with:
A. Operating system files
B. Office documents
C. Network services
D. BIOS

7. Antivirus evasion techniques are used to:
A. Improve detection
B. Avoid antivirus detection
C. Update signatures
D. Patch systems

8. Antivirus software mainly protects against:
A. Hardware failure
B. Malware infections
C. Power outages
D. Network latency

9. Virus detection means:
A. Removing OS
B. Identifying malicious code
C. Blocking network
D. Encrypting files

10. Which malware spreads faster in networks?
A. Virus
B. Worm
C. Trojan
D. Adware

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. Which virus stays resident in system memory?
A. Boot virus
B. File virus
C. Resident virus
D. Macro virus

12. Non-resident viruses:
A. Stay permanently in memory
B. Execute and exit
C. Spread over network
D. Modify boot sector

13. Polymorphic viruses evade detection by:
A. Hiding files
B. Changing code signature
C. Using encryption only
D. Using network ports

14. Metamorphic viruses are harder to detect because they:
A. Encrypt payload
B. Rewrite their own code
C. Use UDP
D. Are small in size

15. Signature-based antivirus detection fails when malware is:
A. Known
B. Unchanged
C. Polymorphic or new
D. Small

16. Heuristic detection works by:
A. Comparing signatures
B. Analyzing suspicious behavior
C. Checking file size
D. Using hashes only

17. Which virus type activates only on a specific condition?
A. Polymorphic virus
B. Stealth virus
C. Logic bomb
D. Resident virus

18. Stealth viruses evade detection by:
A. Deleting files
B. Hiding changes from OS
C. Encrypting network
D. Increasing speed

19. Worms cause more damage than viruses mainly due to:
A. Smaller size
B. Automatic propagation
C. File infection
D. User execution

20. Antivirus updates are important because:
A. Improve UI
B. Add new virus signatures
C. Reduce CPU usage
D. Increase bandwidth

