A. Manual execution
B. Rapid self-propagation
C. Need email
D. Need USB

24. Which detection method is MOST effective against unknown malware?
A. Signature-based
B. Heuristic
C. Static hashing
D. Manual scan

25. A virus that modifies itself each time it runs is:
A. Stealth virus
B. Polymorphic virus
C. Boot virus
D. Macro virus

26. Antivirus sandboxing helps by:
A. Encrypting malware
B. Running files in isolated environment
C. Updating signatures
D. Blocking ports

27. Worms mainly violate which CIA principle?
A. Confidentiality
B. Integrity
C. Availability
D. Authentication

28. Metamorphic malware MOST challenges which detection method?
A. Behavioral
B. Signature-based
C. Sandbox
D. Manual

29. Logic bombs are dangerous because they:
A. Spread automatically
B. Trigger on specific events/time
C. Encrypt network
D. Replicate rapidly

30. Session 14 mainly tests understanding of:
A. Programming
B. Malware classification & detection logic
C. Database tuning
D. Hardware design

